## Content Phases

Every piece of content progresses through seven codified phases. A visible progress indicator shows current phase and completed phases on each piece.

| # | Phase | Who | What Happens | Gate to Next |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Brief** | User | Pick content type → template loads → user edits fields | User marks `ready` |
| 2 | **Research** | AI + User | Claude reviews sources, runs SERP/keyword research, surfaces angles | User approves research notes |
| 3 | **Outline** | AI + User | Claude proposes H2/H3 outline from brief + research | User edits and approves |
| 4 | **Interview** | Guest | Guest opens link, AI conducts async voice interview | Interview `completed` |
| 5 | **Draft** | AI | Claude synthesises transcript + brief + outline into full draft | Draft `ready` |
| 6 | **Edit** | User | Inline editing, section regeneration, formatting refinement | User marks `edited` |
| 7 | **Review** | Admin/creator | Final approval gate before HubSpot push | Approved → push enabled |

Phase progression is **always forward**. A brief cannot skip phases, but the user can loop within a phase (re-interview, regenerate draft, re-outline).

Solo workflows: Review can be auto-completed by the creator (workspace setting).

