## Multi-Language Rules

Every brief has **two language fields**:
- `interviewerLanguage` — drives Deepgram STT config and ElevenLabs TTS voice selection
- `outputLanguage` — drives Claude generation (written into system prompt explicitly)

They can differ. Example: a Norwegian company interviews an English-speaking customer (`interviewerLanguage=en`) for a Norwegian case study (`outputLanguage=no`).

UI language is English only in MVP; Norwegian localisation planned post-MVP.

---

## Workspace & User Model

- Each company/agency = one **workspace**
- Workspace tied to a Polar.sh subscription
- **Unlimited seats** per workspace — pricing is credit-based, not per seat
- Roles:
  - `admin` — manage billing, HubSpot connections, invite users, approve Review phase, configure auto-approval
  - `member` — run briefs through all phases up to Review, submit for approval
- Admins see all workspace content; members see their own + shared

